Title: Why isn't MapDialogRect mapping dialog rectangles?
Description: A customer wanted to convert dialog box units to pixels, and since Get­Dialog­Base­Units is a crock, they switched to using Map­Dialog­Rect. However, they found that Map­Dialog­Rect wasn’t working either: It always returned FALSE. What’s going on? Upon closer inspection, what’s going on is that the customer’s code wasn’t passing a dialog box handle as the first parameter to the Map­Dialog­Rect function.

Title: Willingness to look stupid
Description: People frequently1 think that I'm very stupid. I don't find this surprising, since I don't mind if other people think I'm stupid, which means that I don't adjust my behavior to avoid seeming stupid, which results in people thinking that I'm stupid. Although there are some downsides to people thinking that I'm stupid, e.g., failing interviews where the interviewer very clearly thought I was stupid, I think that, overall, the upsides of being willing to look stupid have greatly outweighed the downsides.
